<section>
  <h3 class="dummy-h3" id="component-api"><a href="#component-api" class="dummy-link-section">§</a> Component API</h3>
  <p class="dummy-paragraph">The
    <code class="dummy-code">Text</code>
    component can be used directly as is, or via one of its specialized "style/size" variants:</p>
  <ul>
    <li class="dummy-paragraph">
      <code class="dummy-code">Text::Display(500|400|300|200|100)</code>
    </li>
    <li class="dummy-paragraph">
      <code class="dummy-code">Text::Body(300|200|100)</code>
    </li>
    <li class="dummy-paragraph">
      <code class="dummy-code">Text::Code(300|200|100)</code>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h4 class="dummy-h4">Text</h4>
  <p class="dummy-paragraph" id="component-api-text">Here is the API for the "base"
    <code class="dummy-code">Text</code>
    component:</p>
  <dl class="dummy-component-props" aria-labelledby="component-api-text">
    <dt>size <code>enum</code></dt>
    <dd>
      <p>The size ("style") for the text.</p>
      <p>Acceptable values:</p>
      <ol>
        {{#each @model.SIZES as |size|}}
          <li class={{if (eq size @model.DEFAULT_SIZE) "default"}}>{{size}}</li>
        {{/each}}
      </ol>
    </dd>
    <dt>tag <code>enum</code></dt>
    <dd>
      <p>The html tag to use in the dynamic render of the component.</p>
      <p>Acceptable values:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>h1</li>
        <li>h2</li>
        <li>h3</li>
        <li>h4</li>
        <li>h5</li>
        <li>h6</li>
        <li>p</li>
        <li>span</li>
        <li>li</li>
        <li>code</li>
        <li>pre</li>
        <li>div</li>
      </ol>
      <p>Notice: the default value, if no
        <code class="dummy-code">@tag</code>
        argument is provided, depends on the
        <code class="dummy-code">@size</code>
        argument:</p>
      <ol class="dummy-text-component-api-defaults">
        {{#each-in @model.MAPPING_SIZE_TO_TAG as |size tag|}}
          <li>{{size}} → &lt;{{tag}}&gt;</li>
        {{/each-in}}
      </ol>
    </dd>
    <dt>weight <code>enum</code></dt>
    <dd>
      <p>The weight of the text.</p>
      <p>Acceptable values:</p>
      <ol>
        {{#each @model.AVAILABLE_WEIGHTS as |weight|}}
          <li>{{weight}}</li>
        {{/each}}
      </ol>
      <p>Notice: only certain combinations of
        <code class="dummy-code">@size</code>
        and
        <code class="dummy-code">@weight</code>
        are recommended; please refer to the examples below to see which one are approved. If you need a different
        combination please speak with the Design System team.</p>
      <p>Notice: the default value, if no
        <code class="dummy-code">@weight</code>
        argument is provided, depends on the
        <code class="dummy-code">@size</code>
        argument:</p>
      <ol class="dummy-text-component-api-defaults">
        {{#each-in @model.DEFAULT_WEIGHTS as |size weight|}}
          <li>{{size}} → {{weight}}</li>
        {{/each-in}}
      </ol>
    </dd>
    <dt>align <code>enum</code></dt>
    <dd>
      <p>The alignment of the text</p>
      <p>Acceptable values:</p>
      <ol>
        {{#each @model.ALIGNS as |align|}}
          <li>{{align}}</li>
        {{/each}}
      </ol>
      <p>If no
        <code class="dummy-code">@align</code>
        argument is provided, the text will simply follow (inherit) the alignment of the parent container.</p>
    </dd>
    <dt>...attributes</dt>
    <dd>
      <p><code class="dummy-code">...attributes</code> spreading is supported on this component.</p>
    </dd>
  </dl>

  <h4 class="dummy-h4">Display[…] / Body[…] / Code[…]</h4>
  <p class="dummy-paragraph" id="component-api-text-styles">The API for the specialized "style/size" variant components
    is exactly the same as the "base"
    <code class="dummy-code">Text</code>
    component, apart from the
    <code class="dummy-code">@size</code>
    argument, which is implicity set by the variant itself (see above for more details on acceptable values and
    defaults).</p>
  <dl class="dummy-component-props" aria-labelledby="component-api-text-styles">
    <dt>tag <code>enum</code></dt>
    <dd>
      <p>The html tag to use in the dynamic render of the component.</p>
    </dd>
    <dt>weight <code>enum</code></dt>
    <dd>
      <p>The weight of the text.</p>
    </dd>
    <dt>align <code>enum</code></dt>
    <dd>
      <p>The alignment of the text</p>
    </dd>
    <dt>...attributes</dt>
    <dd>
      <p><code class="dummy-code">...attributes</code> spreading is supported on this component.</p>
    </dd>
  </dl>

